<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="fr">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="refresh" content={`0; url=${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}fr/`} />
  </head>
  <body>
   <noscript>
      <p><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}fr/`}>Go to homepage</a></p>
    </noscript>
  </body>
</html>

<!--
      Root Redirect (index.astro)

      Purpose:
      - The site has no content at "/" since all pages live under "/fr/" or "/en/".
      - Without this file, visiting the root URL would result in a 404.

      Approach:
      - Use a meta refresh redirect to send users to "/fr/" (default language).
      - Keep <body> empty to avoid flashing a "Redirectingâ€¦" message.

      Benefits:
      - Simplicity: no JavaScript needed.
      - Sustainability: minimal resources (just one extra request).
      - Reliability: works in all browsers, even with JS disabled.
      - UX: no distracting flash on load.
      - Future-proof: if default language changes, only the URL here needs updating.

      Alternatives:
      - JS auto-detect (better UX for EN users, adds complexity).
      - Language chooser page (no redirect, but adds a click).
      - Server-side redirect (ideal, but not supported on GitHub Pages).

      This is the lightest and most standard option for a bilingual static site on GitHub Pages.
    -->